Section.Description: Checks in this section help monitor the result of actions taken over the course of a model’s development, which can directly impact the model’s performance. Proper management of these items can improve model performance.

Check.Description: RESULT of the file sizes for all reported Revit models in MB (megabytes).
COUNT of all warnings in the model. Too many unresolved warnings can cause performance issues in a Revit model.
RESULT and LIST of the families in the project ordered by file size. **WARNING** Running this check can take a significant amount of time, depending on how many loadable families the model has.

COUNT of all elements that can be purged from a Revit model. A large number of unneeded elements can increase the model size with no benefit. Note that the count reported here may differ from the Purge Unused command in the Revit interface due to API restraints.

COUNT and LIST of all non built-in categories and sub-categories in a Revit model. A large number of these items may be indicative of an imported CAD file. Importing CAD files is not recommended for most workflows.
COUNT of all model group elements in the model. Too many model groups can be an indication of improper modeling techniques.
COUNT of all detail group elements in the model. Too many detail groups can be an indication of improper modeling techniques.
COUNT of all in-place family elements in the model. In-place families can signifcantly impact model size and performance and should be used sparingly.

Section.Description: Checks in this section are related to settings that can be configured at a project level, which may need to be verified for compliance with standards defined for the project.

Check.Description: LIST of the version and build data of Revit running the check.
COUNT and LIST of all elements created in each design option of the model.
COUNT and LIST of all elements in each phase of the model.
COUNT and LIST of all user worksets in the model or indicates '*Not Workshared*' if worksharing is not enabled.
COUNT and LIST of all parameters and values attached to Project Information for a project except those associated with Revit Extensions (starting with 'Extensions').
COUNT and LIST of the coordinate values of the survey and project base points, elevation, and true north.
PASS/FAIL check to determine if Latitude value is correct for the project location. Provide degree value in radians (1 deg = 0.0174533 rad). Value is defined by User Input.
Check.FailureMessage: The Latitude value is incorrect for Project Location.

Check.Description: PASS/FAIL check to determine if Longitude value is correct for the project location. Provide degree value in radians (1 deg = 0.0174533 rad). Value is defined by User Input.
Check.FailureMessage: The Longitude value is incorrect for Project Location.

Check.Description: PASS/FAIL check to determine if the Project Base Point is at the designated file origin. Provide input numbers as decimal value up to the nearest 0.00001. Value is defined by User Input.
Check.FailureMessage: The Project Base Point is not at the designated file origin.

Check.Description: COUNT and LIST of all browser organization types in the model.
LIST of all model Volume Computation settings: areas and volumes or areas only.

Section.Description: A series of checks related to linked and imported files in the model.

Check.CheckName: Linked Revit Files and Their Link Method
Check.Description: COUNT and LIST of the link method (overlay vs. attach) for each Revit link in the model.

Check.CheckName: Linked Revit Files Not Pinned in Place
Check.Description: PASS/FAIL check to determine if any linked Revit files are not pinned in place. Will Fail if any are found.
Check.FailureMessage: There are linked Revit models that are not pinned in place.

Check.Description: COUNT and LIST of all linked CAD files in the model.

Check.CheckName: Linked CAD File Visible in All Views
Check.Description: COUNT and LIST of all linked CAD files not set to Current View Only.

Check.CheckName: Linked CAD File Not Pinned in Place
Check.Description: PASS/FAIL check to determine if any linked CAD files are not pinned in place. Will Fail if any are found.
Check.FailureMessage: The following linked DWG files are not pinned in place.

Check.Description: COUNT and LIST of all CAD files that were Imported and not Linked.
COUNT of all imported SKP files in the model.
COUNT and LIST of all raster images placed in the model.

Section.Description: A series of checks related to datum and location elements in the model.

Check.Description: COUNT of all level elements in the model.
Check.FailureMessage: [FAIL MESSAGE]

Check.Description: COUNT and LIST of all level types in the model.
Check.FailureMessage: [FAIL MESSAGE]

Check.Description: COUNT of all grid elements in the model.
Check.FailureMessage: [FAIL MESSAGE]

Check.Description: COUNT and LIST of all grid types in the model.
Check.FailureMessage: [FAIL MESSAGE]

Check.CheckName: Wrong Elements on Shared Levels and Grids
Check.Description: COUNT and LIST of all elements in the model that are on the 'Shared Levels and Grids' workset that are not levels or grids. Note that the 'Shared Levels and Grids' workset must have both 'level' and 'grid' (case insensitive) in the name in order to be recognized.

Check.CheckName: Levels and Grids on Wrong Workset
Check.Description: PASS/FAIL check to determine if any levels or grids are not on the Shared Levels and Grids workset. Will Fail if any are found.
Check.FailureMessage: These levels and grids are not on the Shared Levels and Grids workset

Check.Description: COUNT and LIST of all rooms in the model. This includes unplaced and redundant rooms.
Check.FailureMessage: [FAIL MESSAGE]

Check.Description: PASS/FAIL check to determine if any rooms are unplaced. Will Fail if any are found.
Check.FailureMessage: These rooms are unplaced in the model

Check.Description: PASS/FAIL check to determine if any rooms are in the same location as another room. Will fail if any are found.
Check.FailureMessage: These rooms are redundant in the model

Check.Description: PASS/FAIL check to determine if there are rooms with the same number. Will fail if any are found.
Check.FailureMessage: There are Rooms in the model with the same number

Check.Description: COUNT and LIST of all spaces in the model. This includes unplaced and redundant spaces.
Check.FailureMessage: [FAIL MESSAGE]

Check.Description: PASS/FAIL check to determine if any spaces are unplaced. Will Fail if any are found.
Check.FailureMessage: These spaces are unplaced in the model

Check.Description: PASS/FAIL check to determine any spaces are in the same location as another space. Will Fail if any are found.
Check.FailureMessage: These spaces are redundant in the model

Check.Description: PASS/FAIL check to determine if there are spaces with the same number. Will Fail if any are found.
Check.FailureMessage: There are spaces in the model with the same number

Check.Description: COUNT and LIST of all area schemes in a Revit model.
COUNT and LIST of all area elements in the model. This includes unplaced and redundant areas .
Check.FailureMessage: There are unplaced areas in the model.

Check.Description: PASS/FAIL check for any areas that are not placed, regardless of area scheme.
Check.FailureMessage: There are unplaced areas in the model.

Section.Description: A series of checks related to views in the model.

Check.Description: COUNT of all views in the model. Views typically do not impact model size, but too many unmanaged views can impact user efficiency.
COUNT of all schedules in the model. Schedules typically do not impact model size, but too many unmanaged views can impact user efficiency.
COUNT of all sheets in the model. Sheets typically do not impact model size, but too many unmanaged views can impact user efficiency.
COUNT of all placeholder sheets in the model.
COUNT and LIST of all view templates in the model.

COUNT and LIST of all views in the model that have permanently hidden model elements and the total number of hidden elements. Hiding large numbers of elements in a videw can impact performance. **WARNING** Running this check can take a significant amount of time to complete.
COUNT of all views that have no View Templates assigned to them in the model. This may be indicative of unneeded working views that can be removed from a model.
COUNT and LIST of all views (not including views that can be placed on more than one sheet, like Schedules and Legends) that are not placed on a sheet in the model.

Check.CheckName: Views On Sheets With No View Template
Check.Description: COUNT of all views on sheets that have no view templates assigned to them in the model. Printed views with no view template may be indicative of poorly managed or followed standards in the model, which can lead to less efficient methods of control element appearance.
PASS/FAIL check to determine if there is a 3D view labeled with the word "Navis" for export to Navisworks.
Check.FailureMessage: There is no 3D view labeled with the word "Navis" for export to Navisworks.

Check.Description: COUNT and LIST of all legend views in the model.
COUNT and LIST of all the scope boxes used in the model

Section.Description: A series of checks related to model elements in the model.
Reports of architectural system families in the model

Check.Description: COUNT and LIST of all ceiling family types in the model.
COUNT and LIST of all architectural curtain system family types in the model.
COUNT and LIST of all curtain wall mullion family types in the model.
COUNT and LIST of all floor family types in the model.
COUNT and LIST of all railing family types in the model.
COUNT and LIST of all ramp family types in the model.
COUNT and LIST of all roof family types in the model.
COUNT and LIST of all site family types in the model.
COUNT and LIST of all stair family types in the model.
COUNT and LIST of all wall family types in the model.

Section.Description: Reports of MEP system families in the model

Check.Description: COUNT and LIST of all duct family types in the model.
COUNT and LIST of all duct system family types in the model.

Check.CheckName: Duct Systems That Are Not Connected
Check.Description: PASS/FAIL check to determine if there are any duct related elements that have a blank System Name.
Check.FailureMessage: There are duct related elements that have a blank System Name.

Check.Description: COUNT and LIST of all flex duct family types in the model.
COUNT and LIST of all flex pipe family types in the model.
COUNT and LIST of all pipe family types in the model.
COUNT and LIST of all piping system family types in the model.

Check.CheckName: Piping Systems That Are Not Connected
Check.Description: PASS/FAIL check to determine if there are any piping related elements that have a blank System Name.
Check.FailureMessage: There are piping related elements that that have a blank System Name.

Check.CheckName: Electrical Systems That Are Not Connected
Check.Description: PASS/FAIL check to determine if there are any electrical related elements that have a blank Panel Name or Circuit Number.
Check.FailureMessage: There are electrical related elements that have a blank Panel Name or Circuit Number.

Section.Description: Reports of structural system families in the model

Check.Description: COUNT and LIST of all floor family types in the model.
COUNT and LIST of all foundation family types in the model.
COUNT and LIST of all rebar family types in the model.
COUNT and LIST of all wall family types in the model.

PASS/FAIL check to determine if there are any modeled elements that are duplicates (identical elements at the same location and base level). Check will Fail if any duplicate element is found. **WARNING** Running this check can take a significant amount of time to complete.
Check.FailureMessage: Element is a duplicate at the same location and base level.

Check.Description: PASS/FAIL check to determine if there are mirrored instances of loadable components. Check will fail if any element is mirrored.
Check.FailureMessage: The following elements have been mirrored.

Check.Description: COUNT and LIST of all user worksets for a Revit model or indicates '*Not Workshared*' if worksharing is not enabled.
COUNT and LIST of all assembly elements in the model.
COUNT and LIST of all generic model elements in the model.

COUNT of all model elements placed in the model for Revit 2023. This check is version specific due to changes in Revit categories between versions. This check should be used as a general assessment of the number of elements in the model, as some categories may report sub-elements as individual elements.
Check.FailureMessage: [FAIL MESSAGE]

Section.Description: A series of checks related to annotative elements in the model.

Check.Description: COUNT and LIST of all text styles in the model.
COUNT and LIST of all dimension styles in the model.
COUNT and LIST of all line patterns in model.
COUNT and LIST of all line styles in the model.
COUNT and LIST of all fill patterns in the model.
COUNT and LIST of all filled region types in the model.
COUNT and LIST of all elevation tags in the model.
COUNT and LIST of all section tags in the model.
COUNT of matchlines used in the model.
COUNT and LIST of all view references used in the model.
COUNT and LIST of all keynotes used in the model.
COUNT of all annotative elements placed in the model for Revit 2023. This check is version specific due to changes in Revit categories between version.
Check.FailureMessage: [FAIL MESSAGE]
